reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprised at how much I could fit into it. Very easy to pull. Wheels work well.
reviews.reviewText: Under the seat for short trips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to wipe clean, keeps items organized, and holds more than expected
reviews.reviewText: I recently used this bag on a week-long trip where luggage space was extremely limited. I used compression packing cubes and fit everything I needed for the trip. The padded sleeve inside worked perfectly to hold my Fire tablet and Kindle reader. The outside zipper pocket was great for items I needed easy access to while still being secure. There are enough zipper pockets throughout this bag to ensure all my small items are organized. Pulling this down the aisle of a plane was a little challenging. It does fit, but just barely. It would catch on any legs that were partially in the aisle or anytime I didn’t pull the bag perfectly straight. After a few hangups, I opted to carry it down the aisle. It fit under the seat on all but one of my flights (I had a total of four flights). On one flight, I had an aisle seat with a more narrow under-the-seat storage area. On that flight, I did need to put the bag in the overhead compartment. The telescoping handle moved up and down without any issue, and the wheels rolled smoothly. Overall, I really liked this bag, and it proved ideal for my travel needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was lighter than I thought it would be. Many zippers and spacious. I love the color of mulberry and the fact that it fits easily on my 4 Wheeler. I highly recommend this combination.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is such a great under the seat bag! There are a lot of pockets and storage compartments. Look at the pictures to see how well they incorporated all of the storage into this small bag. The fabric is a nice smooth fabric that looks easy to clean. There is a luggage handle sleeve on the back, a telescoping handle that can adjust to two heights, and even a removable laptop sleeve. One side pocket has a zipper while the other is expandable and can fit my large water bottle. There are also two zippered front compartments in addition to the main compartment. Little details such as a snap to hold the handles together while you are rolling the luggage, were a great addition. I love that this fits the dimension to be a personal item because I always book a basic fair where I’m not allowed to carry on and this is a great way to transport anything extra that doesn’t fit in my luggage if I’m going on a short trip, I could even use this alone For a long weekend away! Excited to try this out next week.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Holds a Lot
reviews.reviewText: This is a very well designed bag, with lots and lots of storage space. One of the outside pockets extends farther, with lots of little pockets inside. The handle collapses and extends very smoothly and its very easy to handle and roll around. I do think it's a bit overpriced, but it is an extremely useful piece of luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Design is Well Thought Out, and Excellent Quality
reviews.reviewText: As with all Baggallini products, the design is well thought out, and the quality is excellent. I use a lot of Baggallinis smaller cross-body purses. To get around the two-bag rule on Southwest, I stash one of those purses inside the bag, it’s very easy to slide under the seat ahead and carry a tote to stash in the overhead. It rolls easily around the airport and turns on a dime. My only hesitation is the price--it's a bit steep for what it is (loses a star).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect! Amazing organization!
reviews.reviewText: This Baggallini 2-Wheel Underseater bag is awesome!This compact and stylish carry-on luggage is perfect for any travel adventure. The two wheels make it easy to maneuver through busy airports, and the underseat design allows me to keep all my essentials close by. The black color is sleek and professional, making it versatile for any occasion. The quality of the material is top-notch and will hold up well on trips. I especially appreciate the expandable feature, providing even more space for everything you need to pack.Overall, I highly recommend the Baggallini 2-Wheel Underseater for its functionality, durability, and chic design. 5 stars all the way!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super cute, well-made, slightly too large for some airlines' carry-on bag sizes.
reviews.reviewText: Adorable little carry-on, nicely made, love the wheeled design that allows you to rest your personal item on top as you breeze through the airport terminal.The sizing in the description is 15 x 14.5 x 9, many airlines publish their carry-on sizing as 22 x 14 x 9, probably totally fine for most legacy carriers, possibly not for the budget carriers that stand there with a tape measure and a box to measure all of your luggage (unless you bought the "all-in" bundle, then they seem to care a whole lot less...) I've got a flight in a few weeks, I'll report back if I get the shakedown at the counter or at the gate, but it should be just fine.
